<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/75092427-tiera-denise"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1514419240i/75092427._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/75092427-tiera-denise">Tiera Denise</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The book would be COMPLETELY different if told from the pov of their men. Self love and friendship are some pretty big themes throughout the book and <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The book would be COMPLETELY different if told from the pov of their men. Self love and friendship are some pretty big themes throughout the book and I feel as if having the pov of the men wouldn't contribute to this at all. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
